nd any issues I have ran into so far. Notables are Firefox and iPod issues.</description>\n<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jan 2007 12:20:03 GMT</pubDate>\n<guid isPermaLink="true">http://digg.com/tech_news/Impressions_of_Windows_Vista_after_One_Month_of_Usage</guid>\n<digg:diggCount>962</digg:diggCount>\n<digg:submitter><digg:username>adspigot</digg:username><digg:userimage>http://digg.com/userimages/adspigot/medium3875.jpg</digg:userimage></digg:submitter>\n<digg:category>Tech Industry News</digg:category>\n<digg:commentCount>141</digg:commentCount>\n</item>\n<item>\n<title>Battle of the Keynotes: Steve Jobs vs. Bill Gates</title>\n<link>http://digg.com/apple/Battle_of_the_Keynotes_Steve_Jobs_vs_Bill_Gates</link>\n<description>What do these contrasting tones, from the two largest icons of the personal computer industry, signal about the companies they created and lead? One is led by an extraordinary visionary who maintains a vice-like grip on operations. The other is led by a revered technophile who is gradually slipping out the back door.</description>\n<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jan 2007 11:30:01 GMT</pubDate>\n<guid isPermaLink="true">http://digg.com/apple/Battle_of_the_Keynotes_Steve_Jobs_vs_Bill_Gates</guid>\n<digg:diggCount>638</digg:diggCount>\n<digg:submitter><digg:username>ndm007</digg:username><digg:userimage>http://digg.com/userimages/ndm007/medium.gif</digg:userimage></digg:submitter>\n<digg:category>Apple</digg:category>\n<digg:commentCount>92</digg:commentCount>\n</item>\n<item>\n<title>LG''s iPhone clone captured on video</title>\n<link>http://digg.com/apple/LG_s_iPhone_clone_captured_on_video</link>\n<description>“GTPH” gives us a hands-on preview of the LG KE850, which looks extremely similar to the iPhone. Technical specifications have not yet been released, but we do know that it sports a 240 x 400 touchscreen display, much like the iPhone. This is definately an iPhone clone.</description>\n<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jan 2007 10:50:01 GMT</pubDate>\n<guid isPermaLink="true">http: