ike the ipod is?” –Calendar program isn’t finished yet, but I did see an “add new event” icon on the placeholder graphic.</description>\n<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jan 2007 08:50:01 GMT</pubDate>\n<guid isPermaLink="true">http://digg.com/apple/Add_View_Event_Icon_on_iPhone_Steve_Jobs_didn_t_show_this_during_Keynote</guid>\n<digg:diggCount>655</digg:diggCount>\n<digg:submitter><digg:username>CLIFFosakaJAPAN</digg:username><digg:userimage>http://digg.com/userimages/cliffosakajapan/medium5296.jpg</digg:userimage></digg:submitter>\n<digg:category>Apple</digg:category>\n<digg:commentCount>52</digg:commentCount>\n</item>\n<item>\n<title>Software Wars</title>\n<link>http://digg.com/linux_unix/Software_Wars_4</link>\n<description>A graphic map depicting the epic struggle of Free and Open Source Software against the Empire of Microsoft!</description>\n<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jan 2007 07:40:02 GMT</pubDate>\n<guid isPermaLink="true">http://digg.com/linux_unix/Software_Wars_4</guid>\n<digg:diggCount>1243</digg:diggCount>\n<digg:submitter><digg:username>Figs</digg:username><digg:userimage>http://digg.com/img/user-medium/user-default.png</digg:userimage></digg:submitter>\n<digg:category>Linux/Unix</digg:category>\n<digg:commentCount>102</digg:commentCount>\n</item>\n<item>\n<title>How SED-TVs Work</title>\n<link>http://digg.com/hardware/How_SED_TVs_Work</link>\n<description>I heard the TWiT crew talking about SED TVs in their latest podcast &amp; didn''t know much about them.  Basically, SED TVs are essentially flat-panel televisions that uses millions of mini CRTs instead of one electron gun.  The picture is supposed to be amazing, but, unfortunately, it appears at least for now the technology is very cost prohibitive.</description>\n<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jan 2007 05:10:02 GMT</pubDate>\n<guid isPermaLink="true">http://digg.com/hardware/How_SED_TVs_Work</guid>\n<digg:diggCount>643</digg:diggCount>\n<digg:submitter><digg:username>amandaw33</digg:username><digg:userimage>http://digg.com/userimages/amandaw33/medium8506.jpg</digg:userimage></digg:submitter>\n<digg:category>Hardware</digg:category>\n<digg:commentCount>77</digg:commentCount>\n</item>\n<item>\n<title>OpenOffice .odt Opened Up - Part 1: Overview</title>\n<link>http://digg.com/software/OpenOffice_odt_Opened_Up_Part_1_Overview</link>\n<description>At this point we have a clear understanding of the subdocument method that OpenOffice applies to its ODF implementation, and we know what top level elements are handled by each subdocument.</description>\n<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jan 2007 04:50:02 GMT</pubDate>\n<guid isPermaLink="true">http://digg.com/software/OpenOffice_odt_Opened_Up_Part_1_Overview</guid>\n<digg:diggCount>383</digg:diggCount>\n<digg:submitter><digg:username>webtickle</digg:username><digg:userimage>http://digg.com/userimages/w/e/b/webtickle/medium8191.PNG</digg:userimage></digg:submitter>\n<digg:category>Software</digg:category>\n<digg:commentCount>20</digg:commentCount>\n</item>\n</channel>\n</rss>', '20070115013505');

